HEADWORD: Spatulate
<hw>Spat"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>spatulatus</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Nat. Hist.)</fld> <def>Shaped like
spatula, or like a battledoor, being roundish, with a long, narrow,
linear base.</def> <altsp>[Also written
<asp>spathulate</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

